---
import Layout from '../../components/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout title="Core Rules — Custom40k Wiki">

<div class="rules-page">

  <!-- ── Hero ──────────────────────────────────────────────────── -->
  <div class="rules-hero">
    <div class="rules-hero-bg" aria-hidden="true"></div>
    <div class="rules-hero-content">
      <div class="rules-seal" aria-hidden="true">
        <svg viewBox="0 0 64 64" width="68" height="68" fill="none">
          <circle cx="32" cy="32" r="30" stroke="#a21217" stroke-width="1.2" fill="rgba(162,18,23,0.06)"/>
          <circle cx="32" cy="32" r="22" stroke="#a21217" stroke-width="0.8" fill="none" stroke-dasharray="3,2"/>
          <polygon points="32,8 35,22 50,22 38,30 42,44 32,36 22,44 26,30 14,22 29,22" fill="rgba(162,18,23,0.15)" stroke="#a21217" stroke-width="1"/>
          <circle cx="32" cy="32" r="5" fill="#a21217" opacity="0.7"/>
        </svg>
      </div>
      <p class="rules-supertitle">Custom40k Reference</p>
      <h1 class="rules-title">Core Rules</h1>
      <p class="rules-meta">v1.255 · Balance 5.03 · FAQ #5: Codex rules override Core Rules</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ── Tab Nav ────────────────────────────────────────────────── -->
  <nav class="tab-bar" role="tablist" aria-label="Core Rules sections">
    <button class="tab-btn tab-active" data-tab="battle" role="tab">Battle Round</button>
    <button class="tab-btn" data-tab="combat" role="tab">Combat</button>
    <button class="tab-btn" data-tab="units" role="tab">Unit Types</button>
    <button class="tab-btn" data-tab="special" role="tab">Special Rules</button>
    <button class="tab-btn" data-tab="weapons" role="tab">Weapon Abilities</button>
    <button class="tab-btn" data-tab="army" role="tab">Army &amp; Allies</button>
    <button class="tab-btn" data-tab="psychic" role="tab">Psychic</button>
  </nav>

  <!-- ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
  <!-- TAB: BATTLE ROUND                                          -->
  <!-- ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
  <div id="tab-battle" class="tab-panel tab-panel--active">

    <div class="phase-grid">
      <div class="phase-card phase-card--1">
        <div class="phase-num">01</div>
        <div class="phase-name">Rally Phase</div>
        <p>Take Leadership tests for units with Battleshock tokens (2D6 ≤ Ld to pass). Pass: remove all tokens. Fail: tokens remain. 2 tokens = Fleeing.</p>
        <div class="sub-rule">
          <strong>Battleshock Tokens</strong>
          <ul>
            <li><span class="badge-inline">1 token — Pinned</span> −1 to hit, movement halved, no Charge bonus.</li>
            <li><span class="badge-inline badge-red">2 tokens — Fleeing</span> Move D6+6″ toward nearest friendly board edge. Can't receive orders. Removed if reaching board edge.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="phase-card phase-card--2">
        <div class="phase-num">02</div>
        <div class="phase-name">Reinforcement Phase</div>
        <p>Roll reinforcement dice equal to the battle round number. Each 4+ brings one unit from reserve.</p>
        <table class="compact-table">
          <thead><tr><th>Round</th><th>Dice</th><th>Auto Units</th></tr></thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr><td>1</td><td>1D6</td><td>—</td></tr>
            <tr><td>2</td><td>2D6</td><td>—</td></tr>
            <tr><td>3</td><td>3D6</td><td>+1</td></tr>
            <tr><td>4</td><td>4D6</td><td>+2</td></tr>
            <tr><td>5</td><td>5D6</td><td>+3</td></tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
        <p class="note">Transports + embarked units count as one reserve. Characters attached to a unit roll together.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="phase-card phase-card--3">
        <div class="phase-num">03</div>
        <div class="phase-name">Command Phase</div>
        <p>Both players assign orders face-down to all units simultaneously. Orders determine what a unit can do in the Action Phase.</p>
        <div class="order-grid">
          <div class="order-pill">Advance</div>
          <div class="order-pill">Charge</div>
          <div class="order-pill">Escape</div>
          <div class="order-pill">Fight</div>
          <div class="order-pill">Move &amp; Shoot</div>
          <div class="order-pill">Stand &amp; Shoot</div>
        </div>
        <p class="note">If one player has more orders, the other gets Skip tokens (1 per 2 extra orders, rounded up).</p>
      </div>

      <div class="phase-card phase-card--4">
        <div class="phase-num">04</div>
        <div class="phase-name">Initiative Phase</div>
        <p>Both players roll 2D6. Higher result wins initiative and activates first in the Action Phase. Ties: player who did NOT have initiative last round wins. First round: whoever finished deploying first.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="phase-card phase-card--5">
        <div class="phase-num">05</div>
        <div class="phase-name">Action Phase</div>
        <p>Players alternate activating one unit at a time, starting with the initiative holder. Each unit carries out its assigned order.</p>
        <p class="note">A unit may move, shoot, and fight in the same round — but each action only once. A unit already activated may still fight if charged later.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Orders detail -->
    <div class="rule-section reveal">
      <div class="section-divider"><span>Orders</span></div>
      <div class="rule-grid">
        <div class="rule-card">
          <div class="rule-name">Advance</div>
          <p>Move up to M. May Advance D6″ extra. Shoot Assault/Pistol/Grenade at −1. Cannot target units in melee.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="rule-card">
          <div class="rule-name">Charge</div>
          <p>Move up to M (max 12″). Declare charge targets. Make a 6″ Charge move to reach them. Gain +1 A or +1 I as Charge bonus. Then resolve Fight.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="rule-card">
          <div class="rule-name">Escape</div>
          <p>Must be in melee. Receive 1 automatic hit per enemy model in range. Gain 2 Battleshock tokens and flee.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="rule-card">
          <div class="rule-name">Fight</div>
          <p>Must be in melee. Resolve the melee combat. Removes orders from all units in the melee.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="rule-card">
          <div class="rule-name">Move &amp; Shoot</div>
          <p>Move up to M. Fire any weapon except Heavy. Cast basic and normal psychic powers.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="rule-card">
          <div class="rule-name">Stand &amp; Shoot</div>
          <p>Cannot move. Fire any weapon including Heavy. −1 to total hit penalty. Cast all psychic powers.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Meta Orders -->
    <div class="rule-section reveal">
      <div class="section-divider"><span>Meta Orders (Defensive Reactions)</span></div>
      <p class="section-note">Triggered in specific situations — not assigned in the Command Phase. Can only be used by units that haven't activated yet this round and are not in melee.</p>
      <div class="rule-grid">
        <div class="rule-card">
          <div class="rule-name">Counter-Attack</div>
          <p>Requires Counter-Attack ability. When declared as a charge target: treated as having executed a Charge order. Must pick Charge bonus before attacker does.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="rule-card">
          <div class="rule-name">Defensive Fire</div>
          <p>When declared as a charge target: fire ranged weapons at the charger at −1 to hit. Attacker auto-passes Leadership during this.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="rule-card">
          <div class="rule-name">Hold Your Ground</div>
          <p>When declared as a charge target: negates the attacker's Charge bonus. At least 50% of charged units must use this to negate the bonus.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="rule-card">
          <div class="rule-name">Take Cover</div>
          <p>When declared as a ranged target: +1 to Saving throws vs ranged attacks and −1 AT until end of enemy activation.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

  </div><!-- /tab-battle -->


  <!-- ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
  <!-- TAB: COMBAT                                                -->
  <!-- ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
  <div id="tab-combat" class="tab-panel">

    <div class="rule-section">
      <div class="section-divider"><span>Ranged Combat Sequence</span></div>
      <ol class="steps-list">
        <li><strong>Choose Targets</strong> — Select targets for all weapons before resolving. At least one model visible and in range. Can't target units in melee.</li>
        <li><strong>Resolve Attacks</strong> — If multiple targets, resolve all attacks vs one unit before moving to next.</li>
        <li><strong>Hit Rolls</strong> — Roll to hit vs model's BS. Roll of 6 always succeeds.</li>
        <li><strong>Wound Rolls</strong> — Roll based on weapon Strength vs target Toughness.</li>
        <li><strong>Saving Throws</strong> — Roll save, subtract weapon AP. Invulnerability save unaffected by AP.</li>
        <li><strong>Damage</strong> — Failed save = damage equal to weapon profile. When damage ≥ Wounds, model removed. Damage doesn't carry over.</li>
        <li><strong>Leadership Test</strong> — If unit drops below half starting strength, pass Ld test or receive 2 Battleshock tokens.</li>
      </ol>
    </div>

    <div class="rule-section reveal">
      <div class="section-divider"><span>Strength vs. Toughness</span></div>
      <table class="ref-table">
        <thead><tr><th>Condition</th><th>To Wound Roll</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td>S ≥ 2×T</td><td class="roll-good">2+</td></tr>
          <tr><td>S &gt; T</td><td class="roll-good">3+</td></tr>
          <tr><td>S = T</td><td>4+</td></tr>
          <tr><td>S &lt; T</td><td class="roll-bad">5+</td></tr>
          <tr><td>S ≤ ½T</td><td class="roll-bad">6+</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
      <p class="note">Strength "D": wound roll of 2+ always succeeds; armor penetration roll of 2+ is always a penetrating hit.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="rule-section reveal">
      <div class="section-divider"><span>Melee Combat Sequence</span></div>
      <ol class="steps-list">
        <li><strong>Defender Movement</strong> — Defender moves up to 6″ to place models in base contact. Characters take priority.</li>
        <li><strong>Initiative Order</strong> — Models act from highest to lowest Initiative. Same Initiative = simultaneous.</li>
        <li><strong>Engagement Range</strong> — Base contact OR within 1″ of a friendly model in base contact. Can fight one level up/down.</li>
        <li><strong>Resolve Attacks</strong> — Distribute A stat freely among melee weapons. Roll vs WS. Roll of 6 always hits.</li>
        <li><strong>Combat Result</strong> — Score: +1 for more remaining wounds, +1 per wound caused, +1 per penetrating hit. Winner = more points.</li>
        <li><strong>Losing Combat</strong> — Loser takes Ld test with penalty = result difference. Fail: 2 Battleshock tokens (flee).</li>
        <li><strong>Pursuit</strong> — Winner may pursue fleeing units: roll D6+highest I. Match or exceed fleeing unit's roll to catch (+1 auto hit per model, −1 Battleshock token from fleeing unit).</li>
      </ol>
      <p class="note">*Vehicle remaining HP count as 5 Wounds each for combat scoring.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="rule-section reveal">
      <div class="section-divider"><span>Cover</span></div>
      <div class="cover-grid">
        <div class="cover-card">
          <div class="cover-title">Light Cover</div>
          <ul><li>+1 Armour Save</li><li>−1 hit to ranged attackers</li><li>−1 AT to incoming ranged</li><li>Example: sandbag barricades</li></ul>
        </div>
        <div class="cover-card">
          <div class="cover-title">Heavy Cover</div>
          <ul><li>+2 Armour Save</li><li>−1 hit to ranged attackers</li><li>−1 AT to incoming ranged</li><li>Example: bunkers</li></ul>
        </div>
        <div class="cover-card">
          <div class="cover-title">Obscuring Terrain</div>
          <ul><li>Cover if line passes through terrain ≥ ½ height &amp; width</li><li>−1 hit for attacker</li><li>No AP penalty or armour save bonus (not treated as cover)</li></ul>
        </div>
      </div>
      <p class="note">Cover requires ≥50% of models/bases to be in it. If both sides benefit from the same terrain, neither gets the bonus. Units in cover that are charged always get Hold Your Ground.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="rule-section reveal">
      <div class="section-divider"><span>Terrain Types</span></div>
      <div class="rule-grid">
        <div class="rule-card">
          <div class="rule-name">Normal Terrain</div>
          <p>No movement restrictions.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="rule-card">
          <div class="rule-name">Difficult Terrain</div>
          <p>Movement penalty: M3″=−1″ / M6″=−2″ / M12″=−4″ / M24″=−8″ (or 33% rounded up). Penalty applies once per activation. Alt: move full speed but treat as dangerous.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="rule-card">
          <div class="rule-name">Dangerous Terrain</div>
          <p>Each model rolls 1D6; each 1 = wound (no saves). Vehicles suffer Engine Damage instead. Test once per activation.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="rule-card">
          <div class="rule-name">Impassable Terrain</div>
          <p>Cannot pass through. Anti-Grav and Jump Pack models may move over it. Cannot end movement on it.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="rule-section reveal">
      <div class="section-divider"><span>Vehicle Damage Chart</span></div>
      <table class="ref-table">
        <thead><tr><th>D6</th><th>Result</th><th>Effect</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td>1</td><td>—</td><td>Nothing happens.</td></tr>
          <tr><td>2</td><td class="result-label">Crew Shaken</td><td>−1 to hit, −50% movement until end of next activation. Not cumulative.</td></tr>
          <tr><td>3</td><td class="result-label">Engine Damage</td><td>Movement reduced by ⅓ permanently. Fully immobilised = can't move, no melee lock. If can't reduce further → lose 1 HP.</td></tr>
          <tr><td>4</td><td class="result-label">Weapon Damage</td><td>Owner chooses a weapon — permanently destroyed. Can spend 1 HP instead of losing last weapon.</td></tr>
          <tr><td>5</td><td class="result-label">Structural Damage</td><td>Lose 1 Hull Point.</td></tr>
          <tr><td>6</td><td class="result-label result-crit">Critical Damage</td><td>Attacker picks: Engine Damage, Weapon Damage, or Structural Damage.</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
      <p class="note">Glancing Hit: roll chart × AT value, apply only highest result (no 6s). Penetrating Hit: roll × AT value, apply ALL results.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="rule-section reveal">
      <div class="section-divider"><span>Mixed Units</span></div>
      <ul class="plain-list">
        <li><strong>Mixed Armour Save:</strong> Use the save value that occurs most. Tie = controlling player chooses. Casualties from failed saves must come from models matching that save first.</li>
        <li><strong>Mixed Toughness:</strong> Use the T value that occurs most. Tie = controlling player chooses.</li>
        <li><strong>Mixed Defensive Rules:</strong> Use the special rule (or lack of one) that occurs most.</li>
        <li><strong>Characters:</strong> Cannot voluntarily take wounds for the unit. Always use their own armour/invul save.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="rule-section reveal">
      <div class="section-divider"><span>Suppressive Fire</span></div>
      <p>Scoring 6+ ranged hits with non-Suppression weapons forces the target to take a Ld test. For every additional 6 hits: cumulative −1 penalty. Fail → 1 Battleshock token (if they had none).</p>
    </div>

  </div><!-- /tab-combat -->


  <!-- ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
  <!-- TAB: UNIT TYPES                                            -->
  <!-- ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
  <div id="tab-units" class="tab-panel">

    <div class="unit-type-grid">

      <div class="unit-type-card">
        <div class="unit-type-header">
          <span class="unit-type-icon">👣</span>
          <span class="unit-type-name">Infantry</span>
          <span class="unit-type-sub">Creature</span>
        </div>
        <p>Follows all standard rules without exceptions. The baseline unit type.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="unit-type-card">
        <div class="unit-type-header">
          <span class="unit-type-icon">🏍</span>
          <span class="unit-type-name">Bike</span>
          <span class="unit-type-sub">Creature</span>
        </div>
        <ul>
          <li>Cannot move vertically on terrain.</li>
          <li>Auto-advances 6″ on Advance order.</li>
          <li>May fire Heavy weapons with Move &amp; Shoot.</li>
          <li>Always fires Rapid Fire at full range.</li>
          <li>Fires all weapon types on Charge at −1.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="unit-type-card">
        <div class="unit-type-header">
          <span class="unit-type-icon">⚜</span>
          <span class="unit-type-name">Character Model</span>
          <span class="unit-type-sub">Creature</span>
        </div>
        <ul>
          <li>Can join a creature unit (start Command Phase within 2″).</li>
          <li>One character per unit. Cannot join Monstrous Creatures or Vehicles.</li>
          <li>Must be targeted separately in melee.</li>
          <li>Auto-rallies during Rally Phase if alone.</li>
          <li>Cannot take wounds for unit in ranged. Uses own armour/invul.</li>
          <li>Fires only one weapon per activation (unless equipment states otherwise).</li>
          <li>Ignored when determining half-strength.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="unit-type-card">
        <div class="unit-type-header">
          <span class="unit-type-icon">🛸</span>
          <span class="unit-type-name">Jet Bike</span>
          <span class="unit-type-sub">Creature</span>
        </div>
        <ul>
          <li>Ignores terrain and vertical movement costs.</li>
          <li>Auto-advances 6″ on Advance order.</li>
          <li>May fire Heavy weapons with Move &amp; Shoot.</li>
          <li>Always fires Rapid Fire at full range.</li>
          <li>Fires all weapon types on Charge at −1.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="unit-type-card">
        <div class="unit-type-header">
          <span class="unit-type-icon">✈</span>
          <span class="unit-type-name">Jump Pack Infantry</span>
          <span class="unit-type-sub">Creature</span>
        </div>
        <ul>
          <li>Ignores terrain and vertical movement costs.</li>
          <li>Gains the Deep Strike special rule.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="unit-type-card">
        <div class="unit-type-header">
          <span class="unit-type-icon">🦖</span>
          <span class="unit-type-name">Monstrous Creature</span>
          <span class="unit-type-sub">Creature</span>
        </div>
        <ul>
          <li>Cannot be joined by a Character Model.</li>
          <li>Cannot enter transport vehicles.</li>
          <li>Rolls additional D6 (Strength + 2D6 total) to penetrate vehicle armour.</li>
          <li>May fire Heavy with Move &amp; Shoot. Always Rapid Fire at full range. All types on Charge at −1.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="unit-type-card">
        <div class="unit-type-header">
          <span class="unit-type-icon">🦣</span>
          <span class="unit-type-name">Monstrous Infantry</span>
          <span class="unit-type-sub">Creature</span>
        </div>
        <ul>
          <li>Cannot be joined by a Character Model.</li>
          <li>Cannot enter transport vehicles.</li>
          <li>Rolls additional D3 (Strength + 1D6 + 1D3 total) to penetrate vehicle armour.</li>
          <li>May fire Heavy with Move &amp; Shoot. Always Rapid Fire at full range. All types on Charge at −1.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="unit-type-card">
        <div class="unit-type-header">
          <span class="unit-type-icon">🤖</span>
          <span class="unit-type-name">Walker</span>
          <span class="unit-type-sub">Vehicle</span>
        </div>
        <ul>
          <li>Treated like vehicles but locked in melee like infantry.</li>
          <li>May change facing during its own initiative step in melee.</li>
          <li>May fire Heavy with Move &amp; Shoot. Always Rapid Fire at full range. All types on Charge at −1.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="unit-type-card">
        <div class="unit-type-header">
          <span class="unit-type-icon">🚂</span>
          <span class="unit-type-name">Vehicle</span>
          <span class="unit-type-sub">Vehicle</span>
        </div>
        <ul>
          <li>Has Front/Side/Rear armour values and Hull Points.</li>
          <li>Auto-passes Leadership tests.</li>
          <li>Tank Shock on Charge: 1 auto hit per inch travelled at Initiative 10.</li>
          <li>Not locked in melee — can be given any order while in melee.</li>
          <li>Cannot shoot if enemy is in base contact.</li>
          <li>Turret weapons: 360°. Chassis weapons: 180°.</li>
          <li>Move &gt;12″: cannot fire any weapons. Move 6–12″: fire 1 weapon.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="unit-type-card unit-type-card--wide">
        <div class="unit-type-header">
          <span class="unit-type-icon">✈</span>
          <span class="unit-type-name">Flyer</span>
          <span class="unit-type-sub">Vehicle</span>
        </div>
        <ul>
          <li>Deployed during Reinforcement phase, anywhere on the battlefield.</li>
          <li>Can only receive Advance (fire 1 weapon) or Move &amp; Shoot (fire all weapons) orders. Cannot activate first in a turn.</li>
          <li>Always counts as having moved 24″ when not in Hover Mode.</li>
          <li>Subtract 12″ from weapon range when shooting at or from flyers. −1 hit penalty when targeting flyers.</li>
          <li>On Advance order: 4+ invulnerability save. Cannot engage or be engaged in melee.</li>
          <li>3 permanent Engine Damage = disabled for one full round, then all Engine Damage removed and redeployed.</li>
          <li><strong>Hover Mode:</strong> Can capture/hold/contest objectives. Must start in hover mode during deployment or enter by not repositioning in reserve phase.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

    </div>

    <div class="rule-section reveal">
      <div class="section-divider"><span>Profile Values Reference</span></div>
      <div class="stat-ref-grid">
        <div class="stat-ref"><span class="stat-letter">M</span><div><strong>Movement</strong> — Speed in inches. "−" = cannot move.</div></div>
        <div class="stat-ref"><span class="stat-letter">WS</span><div><strong>Weapon Skill</strong> — Melee hit roll target. "−" = cannot fight in melee. Max 1+.</div></div>
        <div class="stat-ref"><span class="stat-letter">BS</span><div><strong>Ballistic Skill</strong> — Ranged hit roll target. "−" = cannot shoot. Max 1+.</div></div>
        <div class="stat-ref"><span class="stat-letter">S</span><div><strong>Strength</strong> — Melee wounding power. Max 10 or D.</div></div>
        <div class="stat-ref"><span class="stat-letter">T</span><div><strong>Toughness</strong> — Damage resistance. Max 10.</div></div>
        <div class="stat-ref"><span class="stat-letter">W</span><div><strong>Wounds</strong> — Damage capacity. Excess damage doesn't carry over between models.</div></div>
        <div class="stat-ref"><span class="stat-letter">I</span><div><strong>Initiative</strong> — Melee activation order, highest first. Max 10.</div></div>
        <div class="stat-ref"><span class="stat-letter">A</span><div><strong>Attacks</strong> — Melee attacks per activation. "−" = cannot fight in melee. Max 10.</div></div>
        <div class="stat-ref"><span class="stat-letter">Ld</span><div><strong>Leadership</strong> — Bravery. Uses highest in squad including attached characters. Max 10.</div></div>
        <div class="stat-ref"><span class="stat-letter">Sv</span><div><strong>Save</strong> — Armour protection, modified by weapon AP. Roll of 1 always fails. Max 1+.</div></div>
        <div class="stat-ref"><span class="stat-letter">Inv</span><div><strong>Invulnerability Save</strong> — Not affected by AP. Max 4+ (unless stated otherwise).</div></div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="rule-section reveal">
      <div class="section-divider"><span>Weapon Types</span></div>
      <table class="weapon-types-table">
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th>Type</th>
            <th>Stand &amp; Shoot</th>
            <th>Move &amp; Shoot</th>
            <th>Advance</th>
            <th>Charge</th>
            <th>Fight</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td>Assault</td><td>✓</td><td>✓</td><td>✓</td><td>✓</td><td>—</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Grenade¹</td><td>✓</td><td>✓</td><td>✓</td><td>✓</td><td>✓*</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Heavy</td><td>✓</td><td>—</td><td>—</td><td>—</td><td>—</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Melee²</td><td>—</td><td>—</td><td>—</td><td>✓</td><td>✓</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Pistol³</td><td>✓</td><td>✓</td><td>✓</td><td>✓</td><td>—</td></tr>
