  <div id="tab-special" class="tab-panel">
    <p class="tab-intro">All model special rules from the Core Rules v1.255. Codex rules may add to or override these (FAQ #5).</p>
    <div class="ability-grid">

      <div class="ability-card"><div class="ability-name">Acute Senses</div><p>Infiltrators always stay 18″ apart during deployment, even without direct LOS.</p></div>
      <div class="ability-card"><div class="ability-name">Aegis (X+)</div><p>Dispel any psychic power directly targeting this model on X+. Also prevent Perils of the Warp on X+. Best Aegis in unit applies.</p></div>
      <div class="ability-card"><div class="ability-name">Anti-Grav</div><p>Ignores terrain, units, and vertical movement costs when moving.</p></div>
      <div class="ability-card"><div class="ability-name">Berserk (X+)</div><p>Gain X+ invulnerability save (doesn't work vs S8+). Cannot use Escape or Take Cover.</p></div>
      <div class="ability-card"><div class="ability-name">Blind Rage</div><p>Instead of Battleshock tests: move D6″ toward nearest enemy (may trigger charge). In melee: fail Ld test → lose D3 wounds instead of fleeing. Cannot Escape or Take Cover.</p></div>
      <div class="ability-card"><div class="ability-name">Bodyguard</div><p>Ranged wounds assigned to Bodyguard before characters. Attacks in melee must target Bodyguard first. Can pile in simultaneously with characters.</p></div>
      <div class="ability-card"><div class="ability-name">Brotherhood of Psykers</div><p>If unit has ≥2 models with this rule: +1 to all psychic cast and deny rolls.</p></div>
      <div class="ability-card"><div class="ability-name">Combat Squads</div><p>If unit is at maximum models, may split into two equal units during deployment.</p></div>
      <div class="ability-card"><div class="ability-name">Command Squad</div><p>Models with this ability can join: a squad, a single character, or a squad that already has a character attached.</p></div>
      <div class="ability-card"><div class="ability-name">Counter-Attack</div><p>Model is able to use the Counter-Attack Meta-Order.</p></div>
      <div class="ability-card"><div class="ability-name">Daemon</div><p>The model has a 5+ invulnerability save.</p></div>
      <div class="ability-card"><div class="ability-name">Daemonic Instability</div><p>Ignore effects of 1 Battleshock token. On 2nd token: suffer D3 auto wounds (no saves), discard all tokens, do not flee. In melee: suffer D3+1 auto wounds instead of fleeing. Cannot Escape or Take Cover.</p></div>
      <div class="ability-card"><div class="ability-name">Deep Strike</div><p>When arriving from reserve, place anywhere. Roll scatter die: hit icon = stay, arrow = move 2D6″. If landing on enemy: D6 roll 1–3 back to reserve, 4–6 opponent places unit. Models on terrain take dangerous terrain test.</p></div>
      <div class="ability-card"><div class="ability-name">Deflect</div><p>Ranged attacks against this model suffer −1 to hit rolls.</p></div>
      <div class="ability-card"><div class="ability-name">Fast</div><p>Vehicles double their movement (max 24″). May fire one additional weapon if moved up to 12″.</p></div>
      <div class="ability-card"><div class="ability-name">Fearless</div><p>Automatically passes any Leadership test. Cannot use Escape or Take Cover.</p></div>
      <div class="ability-card"><div class="ability-name">Favoured Enemy</div><p>At game start, choose a faction. Reduce total hit penalty against that faction by −1 (min 0). Leadership tests caused by this model vs that faction suffer cumulative −1.</p></div>
      <div class="ability-card"><div class="ability-name">Frenzy (x″)</div><p>Infantry model gains x″ increased movement for Charge movement.</p></div>
      <div class="ability-card"><div class="ability-name">Furious Charge</div><p>Gain +1 Strength and +1 Initiative until end of battle round when making a charge move.</p></div>
      <div class="ability-card"><div class="ability-name">Greater Daemon</div><p>The model has a 4+ invulnerability save.</p></div>
      <div class="ability-card"><div class="ability-name">Haste (x″)</div><p>Infantry model gains x″ increased movement for Advance movement.</p></div>
      <div class="ability-card"><div class="ability-name">Hit &amp; Run</div><p>After all models in melee activated (before result): unit may move 3D6″ away in straight line. Cannot enter engagement range. Enemy cannot pursue.</p></div>
      <div class="ability-card"><div class="ability-name">Infiltrator</div><p>After all normal deployment, deploy anywhere: 18″ from enemies in LOS, 12″ from enemies out of LOS. Cannot Vanguard move. Alternate placement if both players have Infiltrators.</p></div>
      <div class="ability-card"><div class="ability-name">Massive (X)</div><p>Occupies X additional spaces in transport vehicles.</p></div>
      <div class="ability-card"><div class="ability-name">Mindless</div><p>Auto-passes every Leadership test. Can contest objectives but never hold them.</p></div>
      <div class="ability-card"><div class="ability-name">Move Through Cover</div><p>Does not suffer movement penalties for moving through terrain.</p></div>
      <div class="ability-card"><div class="ability-name">Narthecium</div><p>Once per turn, reduce damage of one wound to the model or its unit by 1 (declared after saves). Doesn't work vs S8+, or Mortal Wounds.</p></div>
      <div class="ability-card"><div class="ability-name">Objective Secured!</div><p>Captured objective remains under control even with no friendly units in range — until opponent contests/conquers it at end of a battle round. Automatically granted to all Troops selections.</p></div>
      <div class="ability-card"><div class="ability-name">Open</div><p>Vehicle has fire hatches = passenger capacity. Passengers can be targeted, cast psychic powers, benefit from cover with transport. Cannot fight in melee while inside. After disembarking, can always make 6″ Charge if vehicle moved ≤12″.</p></div>
      <div class="ability-card"><div class="ability-name">Outflank</div><p>When arriving from reserve, may deploy along side edges (not opponent's deployment zone, not turn 1). Counts as moved at maximum range, Move &amp; Shoot order only.</p></div>
      <div class="ability-card"><div class="ability-name">Parry</div><p>Melee attacks against the model suffer −1 to hit rolls.</p></div>
      <div class="ability-card"><div class="ability-name">Regeneration (X)</div><p>Regains X wounds at the start of each Reinforcement phase.</p></div>
      <div class="ability-card"><div class="ability-name">Retribution (X)</div><p>Melee hits against the model cause X auto wounds per battle round (S4 AP0 D1) against the attacking unit. Multiple models with this rule pool their instances.</p></div>
      <div class="ability-card"><div class="ability-name">Squadron</div><p>All models treated as independent units during deployment. Own orders, no formation requirement.</p></div>
      <div class="ability-card"><div class="ability-name">Stealth</div><p>The model always counts as being in Heavy cover.</p></div>
      <div class="ability-card"><div class="ability-name">Swarm</div><p>Each instance of damage can only cause 1 wound loss. Barrage/Explosive cause 1 hit per remaining Wound on the model.</p></div>
      <div class="ability-card"><div class="ability-name">Tank Hunter</div><p>One armor penetration roll vs vehicle (or wound roll vs Monstrous Creature) may be re-rolled. Multiple models with the same weapon: one roll per model may be re-rolled.</p></div>
      <div class="ability-card"><div class="ability-name">Terrifying (−X)</div><p>Enemy units within 6″ suffer −X Leadership.</p></div>
      <div class="ability-card"><div class="ability-name">Unique</div><p>The weapon or wargear may only be included once per army.</p></div>
      <div class="ability-card"><div class="ability-name">Unyielding</div><p>May fire Heavy with Move &amp; Shoot. Always fires Rapid Fire at full range OR twice at half range. All weapon types at −1 on Charge. Cannot Advance or pursue fleeing units in melee.</p></div>
      <div class="ability-card"><div class="ability-name">Use Cover</div><p>Models benefiting from cover impose an additional −1 to hit rolls for ranged attacks.</p></div>
      <div class="ability-card"><div class="ability-name">Vanguard</div><p>At the start of the first battle round: move 6″ (or 12″ from a transport). Alternate activation with opponent's Vanguard units, starting with the player who deployed first.</p></div>
      <div class="ability-card"><div class="ability-name">Warded</div><p>Gain a 6+ invulnerability save, or improve existing invul by +1 (max 4+). Cumulative with itself.</p></div>

    </div>
  </div><!-- /tab-special -->


