  <div id="tab-weapons" class="tab-panel">
    <p class="tab-intro">Weapon ability keywords that appear in weapon profiles. Codex entries may define additional faction-specific abilities.</p>
    <div class="ability-grid">

      <div class="ability-card"><div class="ability-name">Ammo (X)</div><p>This weapon can only be used X times per game.</p></div>
      <div class="ability-card"><div class="ability-name">Anti-Air</div><p>Attacks vs Anti-Grav, Jet Bike, Jump Pack models or Flyers gain +1 to hit and +1 Strength.</p></div>
      <div class="ability-card"><div class="ability-name">Armorbane</div><p>Rolls an additional 1D6 for armor penetration.</p></div>
      <div class="ability-card"><div class="ability-name">Armor Piercing (X+)</div><p>Wound rolls of X+ always succeed and gain −2 AP. Armor penetration rolls of X+ gain +1 AT and roll an extra 1D3 for armor penetration.</p></div>
      <div class="ability-card"><div class="ability-name">AT (X)</div><p>Can cause Penetrating Hits. On a penetrating hit, roll X dice on the Vehicle Damage Chart and apply all results.</p></div>
      <div class="ability-card"><div class="ability-name">Barrage</div><p>Successful hit → up to 5 additional hits (6 total, if enough models). Failed hit → re-roll once for up to 2 additional hits (3 total). Each model only hit once per shot.</p></div>
      <div class="ability-card"><div class="ability-name">Beam</div><p>Choose target, make normal hit roll. If hit: draw a line from shooting model's base to target. Make wound roll vs target AND any unit the line passes through.</p></div>
      <div class="ability-card"><div class="ability-name">Blind</div><p>If weapon scores at least one hit, target unit does not gain a Charge bonus for its Charge order.</p></div>
      <div class="ability-card"><div class="ability-name">Blood Drinker</div><p>When the model causes a Wound loss, it regains 1 Wound (up to starting value).</p></div>
      <div class="ability-card"><div class="ability-name">Bomb</div><p>Range unaffected by the −12″ range reduction for Flyers.</p></div>
      <div class="ability-card"><div class="ability-name">Combi</div><p>Combines two weapon profiles. Can fire both simultaneously at same target at −1 to hit.</p></div>
      <div class="ability-card"><div class="ability-name">Deadly (X+)</div><p>Wound rolls of X+ increase the Damage value of the attack by +1.</p></div>
      <div class="ability-card"><div class="ability-name">Decimate</div><p>Wound rolls gain +1. Does not work against Vehicles.</p></div>
      <div class="ability-card"><div class="ability-name">Deflagrate (X+)</div><p>Hit rolls of X+ score an additional hit.</p></div>
      <div class="ability-card"><div class="ability-name">Explosive</div><p>Successful hit → up to 3 additional hits (4 total). Failed hit → re-roll once for up to 1 additional hit (2 total). Each model only hit once per shot.</p></div>
      <div class="ability-card"><div class="ability-name">Extra Attack (X)</div><p>Weapon profile can be used an extra X times per activation in addition to other weapons. Maximum X attacks with this weapon per battle round.</p></div>
      <div class="ability-card"><div class="ability-name">Flames</div><p>Weapon hits automatically. Units in cover reduce their cover armour save bonus by cumulative −1 (min 0).</p></div>
      <div class="ability-card"><div class="ability-name">Flurry (X)</div><p>Model makes X additional attacks with this weapon's profile per battle round (can still make more attacks with this weapon).</p></div>
      <div class="ability-card"><div class="ability-name">Force Weapon</div><p>If bearer successfully manifests ≥1 psychic power during activation, this weapon gains +1 Damage for the rest of the battle round.</p></div>
      <div class="ability-card"><div class="ability-name">Grav</div><p>Unless already better, wound roll = enemy's armour save. Unless already worse, enemy's armour save against this = 5+. Does not work vs Vehicles.</p></div>
      <div class="ability-card"><div class="ability-name">Graviton</div><p>Creatures hit must pass Strength test or suffer S4 AP0 D1 Seeking wound (in addition to normal hit). If target in cover and ≥1 hit: terrain becomes difficult and dangerous until next activation.</p></div>
      <div class="ability-card"><div class="ability-name">Gruesome</div><p>Each wound caused counts as two for combat resolution. Fleeing models caught by pursuit suffer one additional automatic wound.</p></div>
      <div class="ability-card"><div class="ability-name">Haywire</div><p>Each hit causes one automatic penetrating hit against a Vehicle (in addition to normal damage). Does not work vs Creatures.</p></div>
      <div class="ability-card"><div class="ability-name">Indirect</div><p>Does not require LOS. Target only gets cover bonus if in a terrain zone. Can only be fired with Stand &amp; Shoot order.</p></div>
      <div class="ability-card"><div class="ability-name">Lance (+X)</div><p>Armor penetration rolls gain +X bonus.</p></div>
      <div class="ability-card"><div class="ability-name">Life Curse</div><p>One wound roll may be re-rolled against Creatures. Multiple models with same weapon: one wound roll per model may be re-rolled.</p></div>
      <div class="ability-card"><div class="ability-name">Master-crafted</div><p>One hit roll may be re-rolled (or wound/AP roll for Barrage/Explosive/Flames). Multiple models: one roll per model. Cannot be used on Grenade weapons with Ammo(X).</p></div>
      <div class="ability-card"><div class="ability-name">Melta</div><p>At half range: +1 Damage, +2 AT, and roll an extra 1D6 for armor penetration.</p></div>
      <div class="ability-card"><div class="ability-name">Monofilament</div><p>If target in cover and ≥1 hit: terrain becomes difficult and dangerous until end of target's next activation.</p></div>
      <div class="ability-card"><div class="ability-name">Overheating</div><p>Each roll of 1 on a hit roll → user suffers a Mortal Wound (or glancing hit for vehicles, using weapon's AT). Re-rolls: initial roll determines overheating. Auto-hit weapons: roll of 1 to wound instead triggers this.</p></div>
      <div class="ability-card"><div class="ability-name">Poison (X+)</div><p>Wound rolls of X+ against Creatures always succeed.</p></div>
      <div class="ability-card"><div class="ability-name">Precision (X+)</div><p>Successful hit rolls of X+ automatically wound Creatures. Cannot be used with Barrage or Explosive.</p></div>
      <div class="ability-card"><div class="ability-name">Psi-shock</div><p>If creature unit is hit, a random psyker in that unit must pass a Ld value test or suffer D3 Mortal Wounds. Vehicles: random psyker suffers D3 Critical Damage instead. Each additional hit from same unit = cumulative −1. Triggers once per activating unit.</p></div>
      <div class="ability-card"><div class="ability-name">Quick (+X)</div><p>The model gains +X to its Initiative.</p></div>
      <div class="ability-card"><div class="ability-name">Rending (X+)</div><p>Wound rolls of X+ gain an additional −1 AP.</p></div>
      <div class="ability-card"><div class="ability-name">Seeking</div><p>Enemy units in cover do not gain any cover benefit and are treated as being outside cover.</p></div>
      <div class="ability-card"><div class="ability-name">Shield Breaker (−X)</div><p>Invulnerability saves of enemy models are degraded by −X.</p></div>
      <div class="ability-card"><div class="ability-name">Shred</div><p>May re-roll to wound rolls with this weapon.</p></div>
      <div class="ability-card"><div class="ability-name">Slow (−X)</div><p>The model suffers −X to its Initiative.</p></div>
      <div class="ability-card"><div class="ability-name">Soul Burn (X+)</div><p>Wound rolls of X+ against Creatures inflict 1 Mortal Wound. Does not work vs Vehicles.</p></div>
      <div class="ability-card"><div class="ability-name">Sunder (X)</div><p>Enemy units in cover reduce their cover armour save bonus by −X (min 0).</p></div>
      <div class="ability-card"><div class="ability-name">Suppression</div><p>1 ranged hit forces target to take a Ld test. Additional Suppression weapons vs same target: cumulative −1. Explosive: +−1. Barrage: +−2. Fail = 1 Battleshock token (if unit has none). Stacks with Suppressive Fire penalties.</p></div>
      <div class="ability-card"><div class="ability-name">Unwieldy</div><p>Model does not gain the +1 Attack for having a pistol in melee. Each model may carry only one Unwieldy item.</p></div>

    </div>
  </div><!-- /tab-weapons -->


