    <div class="rule-section reveal">
      <div class="section-divider"><span>Setting Up Units</span></div>
      <ul class="plain-list">
        <li>Both players alternate deploying one unit at a time (roll-off to determine who goes first).</li>
        <li>Units are deployed within the player's deployment zone unless special rules state otherwise.</li>
        <li>Units held in reserve are declared before deployment begins.</li>
        <li>Infiltrators deploy after all normal deployment is complete.</li>
        <li>Vanguard moves occur at the start of the first battle round before orders are assigned.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

  </div><!-- /tab-army -->


  <!-- ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
  <!-- TAB: PSYCHIC                                               -->
  <!-- ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
  <div id="tab-psychic" class="tab-panel">

    <div class="rule-section">
      <div class="section-divider"><span>Casting Psychic Powers</span></div>
      <ul class="plain-list">
        <li>Models with the <strong>Psyker</strong> rule can manifest psychic powers.</li>
        <li>Powers are classified as <strong>Basic</strong>, <strong>Normal</strong>, or <strong>Complex</strong> — see each order for which categories can be cast.</li>
        <li>Roll 2D6. Result must meet or exceed the power's cast value.</li>
        <li>Casting the same power again in the same turn: −1 cumulative penalty per attempt.</li>
        <li>Requires LOS to target unless stated otherwise.</li>
        <li>Psykers have access to the General Disciplines and their Codex disciplines.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="rule-section reveal">
      <div class="section-divider"><span>Overchanneling</span></div>
      <p>May roll an extra die (3D6 total) when manifesting a power. Suffers D3 Mortal Wounds on any double (in addition to any Perils of the Warp).</p>
    </div>

    <div class="rule-section reveal">
      <div class="section-divider"><span>Dispelling</span></div>
      <p>Some models may dispel powers. If an enemy psyker within 24″ successfully manifests a power: roll 2D6. Result must be <em>greater</em> than the psychic test result to dispel. Dispelled powers have no effect.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="rule-section reveal">
      <div class="section-divider"><span>Psychic Powers in Melee</span></div>
      <ul class="plain-list">
        <li>Psykers in melee can only cast <strong>basic</strong> psychic powers during their initiative phase.</li>
        <li>Targets limited to: the psyker, or friendly/enemy units in the same melee.</li>
        <li>Psykers not in melee cannot target units in melee with Witchfire powers.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="rule-section reveal">
      <div class="section-divider"><span>Hymns, Invocations &amp; Prayers</span></div>
      <p>Cannot be dispelled. May only be attempted once per battle round per unit. If the user is eliminated, effects persist until the Rally phase of the next battle round.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="rule-section reveal">
      <div class="section-divider"><span>Perils of the Warp</span></div>
      <p>Triggered on a double 1 or double 6 during the psychic test. Roll 1D6:</p>
      <table class="ref-table">
        <thead><tr><th>D6</th><th>Name</th><th>Effect</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td>1</td><td class="result-label">Sucked into the Warp</td><td>Pass Ld value test: 1 Mortal Wound. Fail: removed as casualty.</td></tr>
          <tr><td>2</td><td class="result-label">Mindsteal</td><td>1 Mortal Wound. The attempted power cannot be used for the rest of the game.</td></tr>
          <tr><td>3</td><td class="result-label">Power Drain</td><td>1 Mortal Wound. Roll 1D3: both players subtract result from all psychic tests for the rest of the round (cumulative).</td></tr>
          <tr><td>4</td><td class="result-label">Psionic Feedback</td><td>1 Mortal Wound.</td></tr>
          <tr><td>5</td><td class="result-label">Empyrian Aftermath</td><td>Fail Ld value test: 1 Mortal Wound.</td></tr>
          <tr><td>6</td><td class="result-label result-good">Warp Boost</td><td>Pass Ld value test: +1 to hit and +1 to wound rolls until end of next activation. Fail: 1 Mortal Wound.</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
      <p class="note">Vehicles use Leadership 10 for Perils tests. Fearless models still must pass Leadership <em>value</em> tests.</p>
    </div>

  </div><!-- /tab-psychic -->

</div><!-- /rules-page -->
</Layout>

<script is:inline>
(function () {
  var btns = document.querySelectorAll('.tab-btn');
  var panels = document.querySelectorAll('.tab-panel');
  btns.forEach(function (btn) {
    btn.addEventListener('click', function () {
      var id = btn.getAttribute('data-tab');
      btns.forEach(function (b) { b.classList.remove('tab-active'); });
      panels.forEach(function (p) { p.classList.remove('tab-panel--active'); });
      btn.classList.add('tab-active');
      var panel = document.getElementById('tab-' + id);
      if (panel) { panel.classList.add('tab-panel--active'); }
    });
  });
})();
</script>

<style>
